  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Vincent's Word Studies",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Consented (συγκατατεθειμένος)",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Only here in New Testament. Another of Luke's numerous compounds. The Greek student will be struck with the array of compounds, from Luke 23:49 to Luke 23:56, inclusive. The verb means to put (τίθημι), down (κατά), along with (σύν). Hence to put down the same vote or opinion with another: to agree with or assent to. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "Only here in New Testament. Another of Luke's numerous compounds. The Greek student will be struck with the array of compounds, from ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Luke 23:49",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " to ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Luke 23:56",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ", inclusive. The verb means to put (τίθημι), down (κατά), along with (σύν). Hence to put down the same vote or opinion with another: to agree with or assent to. ",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
